00:47:43.470 --> 00:47:45.080
Where do the names come from?

00:47:45.080 --> 00:47:48.680
"Infra," in Latin,
means "below"--

00:47:48.680 --> 00:47:50.000
below red.

00:47:50.000 --> 00:47:53.160
So therefore, the term "infra"
refers to what, the frequency

00:47:53.160 --> 00:47:54.258
or the wavelength?

00:47:59.520 --> 00:48:00.830
The frequency, right?

00:48:00.830 --> 00:48:04.770
Infrared has longer
wavelengths than visible,

00:48:04.770 --> 00:48:08.490
and therefore it has
smaller frequencies.

00:48:08.490 --> 00:48:12.170
So it is below the
red in frequency.

00:48:12.170 --> 00:48:15.400
"Ultra," of course, means
higher, also in Latin,

00:48:15.400 --> 00:48:19.770
so "ultraviolet" means higher
frequencies than violet light.

00:48:19.770 --> 00:48:22.980
Not "violent" light,
but "violet" light.

00:48:22.980 --> 00:48:27.740
OK, and the major
difference, if you

00:48:27.740 --> 00:48:30.620
look at light
propagation in free space

00:48:30.620 --> 00:48:33.890
it doesn't really matter which
wavelength you are considering.

00:48:33.890 --> 00:48:35.720
But of course, the
interaction with matter

00:48:35.720 --> 00:48:38.900
is radically different as
you change wavelengths.

00:48:38.900 --> 00:48:42.500
So it is similar to the question
you asked about electrons.

00:48:42.500 --> 00:48:45.680
It is also true for
microwaves, or even

00:48:45.680 --> 00:48:47.920
for electromagnetic
waves themselves.

00:48:47.920 --> 00:48:51.410
The way visible light
interacts with matter

00:48:51.410 --> 00:48:55.730
is very different than
microwaves and RF waves,

00:48:55.730 --> 00:48:57.970
and it is also very
different than X-rays.

00:48:57.970 --> 00:49:00.920
So X-rays are actually
the next highest

00:49:00.920 --> 00:49:06.350
in frequency after ultraviolet,
and even higher in frequency

00:49:06.350 --> 00:49:07.460
are gamma rays.

00:49:07.460 --> 00:49:10.010
And I guess we stop there.

00:49:10.010 --> 00:49:11.680
But actually, we don't stop.

00:49:11.680 --> 00:49:13.970
The frequency can go, in
principle, all the way

00:49:13.970 --> 00:49:14.570
to infinity.

00:49:14.570 --> 00:49:19.070
But the gamma rays is the
highest that we can observe.

00:49:19.070 --> 00:49:21.140
Now, I promised to
do a calculation

00:49:21.140 --> 00:49:25.850
of the energy-- how much
energy is carried by a photon.

